{
  "texts": [
    "An action transformer treats the feature graph for each particular topic as a query and the features from adjacent frames as keys and values.",
    "As shown in Fig. 20, the video footage is taken as the input, and the backbone network (usually the initial layer of I3D) is used to generate the spatiotemporal feature representation.",
    "The central frame of the feature map generates the bounding box proposal through the RPN, the feature map (filled with positional embedding) and each proposal obtains the proposal's characteristics through the \"head\" network.",
    "The head network is made up of action transformer units (Tx units) to generate the features to be categorized.",
    "QPr and FFN refer to the query preprocessor and feedforward network, respectively."
  ]
}